      "id": "PopularPost353608",
      "post_content": "If you think this card works properly in the rules, you don't understand the problem.   \n  \nIf I use this ability, and then the spell is redirected to point to a non-land target, technically the effect has no valid behaviour. Only errata can save it, and you have errata for every behaviour that comes up. Not to mention that strictly speaking, this effect is Schroedingers cat. If it counters the effect, the effect wouldn't destroy a land so this should fizzle, but then the effect would destroy a land so it won't fizzle and continue until bored.",
      "posted_by": "deworde2510",
